	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				THIS IS FOR ALL YOU PEOPLE THAT HAVE BEEN UNABLE TO MAKE THE TRUESHOT EVEN WITH FLETCHING SKILLS OF 100+:<BR>
<BR>
I have attempted to make this bow nearly 20 times now, at Fletching skills ranging from 103-150.  I'm now at 164 and am going to try again, but here's why I (and many of you out there) have yet to make it:<BR>
<BR>
The stats for the Trueshot Longbow are 20/45 and 100 range.  That's only 50 range less than the HARDEST bow to fletch in the game, the Compound Darkwood Bow (using Linen string) which is 20/45 150 range and NEVER TRIVIALS and has around a 40% success rate at a Fletch level of 202 (the highest).  The Trueshot is an extremely tough bow to fletch, and very decent bow up until the mid 30s, where you could retrieve a better bow from the likes of Velious.<BR>
<BR>
All the young Rangers listed below who claim that they made their Trueshots at Fletch levels of 30 or so are one of the following:<BR>
1. OUTRIGHT LIARS<BR>
2. UNGODLY, INCREDIBLY LUCKY<BR>
<BR>
So don't get discouraged if you can't make this bow after 100,001 tries.  You're lucky if you can make it at all and the ones who do it easily are the exception, not the rule.  I wrote this because I saw all the claims about making the bow at Fletch 40 or so and was really disappointed when I couldn't make it at first.<BR>
<BR>
Jo'Brill Solwynd<BR>
24th Cycle Half-Elven Ranger of Tunare<BR>
Protector of the Pine and Slayer of Gnolls<BR>
Revered Souls Guild<BR>
Morell-Thule Server<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
